    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-04-05T22:36:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-04-05T22:36:00-05:00" n="1030"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1030">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.113/343.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.—Paraphrases.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-04-05T21:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 5, 1912—9 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Government seems under the impression that we are not considering Mexico as a
                    civilized nation, which view, however, erroneous, will be dissipated by
                    accepting their program in regard to duty on shipment of arms, which, as far as
                    I can see, involves no principle. Therefore it has this evening been agreed that
                    the consignment of arms and 250,000 rounds of ammunition should be admitted
                    subject to duties, which will be paid by American colony; that the bill of
                    lading should be assigned to a committee of the American colony named by me to
                    receive and distribute the arms; and that I shall direct the return of the
                    remaining ammunition to consignor at New York City.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
